  "title": "Senior Executive, Academic & Residential Experience",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Senior Executive (ARE) will support the Academic & Residential Experience (ARE) unit in administrative and operational tasks to advance student development through co-curricular activities, managing academic and scholar-related clubs, and hall councils.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Administer Student Community Engagement (ARE) programmes and projects by processing applications, submitting claims and reimbursements, and generating accurate reports to support decision-making</li><li>Manage procurement and asset tracking for clubs and hall councils to ensure timely and compliant purchases aligned with budgetary guidelines</li><li>Maintain and update Student Community Engagement databases to provide reliable data for management and operational reporting</li><li>Develop and coordinate communication of ARE publicity materials and maintain publicity portals to enhance student engagement and awareness</li><li>Coordinate facilities booking requests efficiently to support smooth execution of student activities</li><li>Provide comprehensive administrative support including arranging meetings, recording minutes, and assisting at SAO events to facilitate effective team collaboration</li><li>Plan proactively by anticipating operational needs, taking ownership of assigned tasks, and recommending improvements to enhance administrative processes</li><li>Manage multiple concurrent tasks with adaptability to changing priorities while maintaining high organizational standards</li><li>Collaborate effectively with team members and stakeholders through strong interpersonal communication to foster a supportive work environment</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office applications, especially Excel and Power Automate, to automate workflows and manage data efficiently</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Experience of 1-2 years in programme or project administration including budget processing, funding claims, reimbursements, and reporting to support operational effectiveness</li><li>Degree or Diploma in any discipline; fresh school leavers are welcome to apply</li></ul><p><strong>Other Information</strong></p><ul><li>Contract Period: 1-year</li><li>Location: Boon Lay / Nanyang Avenue</li><li>Working Days: Mondays to Fridays, office hours</li></ul><p>EA License No: 96C4864<br />Reg. No.: R24121728 EUNICE WOO JING QI</p>",
